386→                        <div id="content">Let $k\geq 2$ and let $g_k(n)$ be the largest possible size of $A\subseteq \{1,\ldots,n\}$ such that every $m$ has $&#60;k$ solutions to $m=a_1a_2$ with $a_1&#60;a_2\in A$.<br><br>Is it true that\[g_3(n)=\frac{\log\log n}{\log n}n+(c+o(1))\frac{n}{\log n}\]for some constant $c$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/796">#796</a>: <a href="#cite-Er69-796" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er69','796'); return false;">[Er69,p.80]</a></div>
